message:
Guys please help
I have a Router (with wifi disabled) connected through LAN to an AP and then the rest of home devices connected to the AP
I'm feeling something weird with the connection so I decided to make sure I'm not hacked
I changed the wifi password so now only my laptop is able to connect
Shouldn't I have just 1 MAC Address in the picture?
when I refresh the second mac address  goes away then I refresh and it comes back.

data.message: May be it is the router/AP itself?
The second one should be the router's MAC address, most of the TP-LINK routers shows their MAC as a connected device.
